7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to S.P. 613,
9 L.D. 1529, “An Act to Enhance the Protection of High-value Natural Resources Statewide”
10 Amend the amendment by striking out all of sections 4 and 5 and inserting the
11 following:
12 'Sec. 4. Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry to develop
13 comprehensive report on statewide strategies to enhance conservation of late-
14 successional forests and old-growth forests. Subject to the availability of funds, the
15 Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, referred to in this section as "the
16 department," may develop a comprehensive report on statewide strategies to enhance the
17 conservation of late-successional forests and old-growth forests, including the management
18 of transitioning late-successional forests. In developing the strategies, the department may
19 incorporate ecological values, carbon sequestration methods and economic considerations
20 from a broad range of perspectives to include forest landowners, forest industry
21 representatives, logging contractors, conservation interests and local economies. By
22 November 4, 2026, the department may submit the report, including any recommendations,
23 to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over agriculture,
24 conservation and forestry matters, which may report out legislation related to the report to
25 the 133rd Legislature in 2027. In completing the report under this section, the department
26 may solicit and use resources from other state agencies and outside sources.'
27 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
28 section number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment authorizes, rather than requires, the Department of Agriculture,
3311 Conservation and Forestry to develop a report on statewide strategies to enhance
3322 conservation of late-successional forests and old-growth forests, subject to availability of
